Dr. Austan D. Goolsbee, Chairman of the President's Council of Economic Advisers, has announced his plans to return to his position as a professor at the University of Chicago Graduate School of Business. Prior to his time in the Obama Administration, Goolsbee was a professor at the University of Chicago for fourteen years. President Obama praised Goolsbee's work, stating that he has helped steer the country out of the worst economic crisis since the Great Depression. Goolsbee expressed his pride in working for the President and believes that his commitment to the American people has made a tremendous difference for the nation. In addition to his role as Chairman of the Council of Economic Advisers, Goolsbee also served as a staff economist for the President's Economic Recovery Advisory Board and as a senior adviser to the President's Council on Jobs and Competitiveness.